<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Angry" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Angry,</orth> feeling or showing anger, provoked, properly and tropically: <bibl n="shak. ven 70" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 70" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 70</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 388" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 388</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 388" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 388</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 388" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 388</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 147.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 147, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 1, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">4, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.4.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 4, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.213" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 213</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.207" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.131" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.131" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 131</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.323" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 323</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.203" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 203</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.210.203" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 210</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.210.203" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 210</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.173" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 173</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.268" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 268</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.107" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.168" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.9" default="NO" valid="yes">7, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.2.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 2, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.125" default="NO" valid="yes">2, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.134" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.126" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 74</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.309" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 309</bibl> etc. etc. Followed by <emph>at</emph> and <emph>with</emph> (more frequently by the latter) indiscriminately: <cit><quote>I am so a. at these abject terms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'm a. at him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 3, 13</bibl></cit>. <emph>were he more a. at it</emph> (sc. the commonwealth) <bibl n="shak. cor 4.6.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 6, 14</bibl>. -- <cit><quote>be not a. with me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I should be a. with you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.217" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 217</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>be not a. with the child,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.36" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 36</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>art thou a.? what, with me?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he makes me a. with him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 141</bibl></cit>. And on the other hand: <cit><quote>the heavens with that we have in hand are a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 3, 5</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>who therewith a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 40</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. with my fancy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 27</bibl></cit>.<lb />Trisyllabic in <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 57</bibl>: <emph>but who is man that is not a.?</emph>
